"72:11:3" : {s: 72, a: 11, w: 3, r: "صلح", t: "ٱلصَّٰلِحُونَ", l: "صَٰلِح", lc: 65, tl: "l-ṣāliḥūna", lb: "সৎকর্মশীল",e: "(are) the righteous", b: "সৎকর্মশীল", i: "orang-orang yang saleh", f: 3, rm: "to be right/good/honest/upright/sound/righteous, suit, fit. aslaha - to set a thing aright, reform, do good. saalihaat - good works, fit and suiting deeds. aslaha (vb. 4) - to make whole sound, set things right, effect an agreement between, render fit. islaah - uprightness, reconciliation, amendment, reformation. muslihun - reformer, one who is upright, righteous, a person of integrity, peacemaker, suitable.", ag: "ال التعريف وأسم فاعل", eg: "Determiner al and Noun Active participle", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACT_PCPL", qual: "NOM", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "صَلَحَ،إِصْلَاحٌۭ،صَٰلِحٌ،مُصْلِحُونَ،يُصْلِحُ"},
